{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"26bd612f-40e3-420a-a0e0-0a4802637a44","content":"This is a TUnit project using Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP). Since the project has `<OutputType>Exe</OutputType>`, run it with:\n\n```\ndotnet run --project TestProject.csproj -- --treenode-filter \"/**/SmsNotificationTests/**\"\n```\n\n- `--` separates `dotnet run` args from MTP args\n- `--treenode-filter` is the MTP filter mechanism TUnit uses\n- `\"/**/SmsNotificationTests/**\"` matches all tests under the `SmsNotificationTests` class\n\nThis will run `SendSms_HealthCheck` and `SendSms_ValidPhone_Succeeds`, skipping the `EmailNotificationTests`.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"0b1b3a87-1f90-4198-b272-2755104b515e","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"This is a TUnit project (v0.6.120). TUnit uses Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP) natively. For MTP-based runners, the filter syntax is different from VSTest.\n\nFor TUnit with MTP, to filter by class name, you'd use `--treenode-filter` with the appropriate syntax.\n\nThe TUnit treenode filter syntax for filtering by class is:\n```\n/**/*[SmsNotificationTests]\n```\n\nOr more precisely:\n```\n--treenode-filter \"/*/*/SmsNotificationTests\"\n```\n\nActually, let me think about this more carefully. TUnit uses Microsoft.Testing.Platform. The filter syntax for MTP with TUnit uses `--treenode-filter`.\n\n\nThe treenode filter format follows a path-like structure with segments for assembly, namespace, class, and method. Since TUnit projects compile to executables, they're typically run with `dotnet run`, though `dotnet test` also works. To filter by the `SmsNotificationTests` class, I'd use a pattern that matches the class name within the treenode hierarchy. I'm working through the exact syntax for TUnit's treenode filter under Microsoft.Testing.Platform, trying to nail down whether it uses wildcards like `*` or bracket notation like `[*SmsNotificationTests*]`, and what the precise path hierarchy should be for filtering by class name.","outputTokens":1229},"id":"1b9e18c4-02c6-4081-b2f1-80115cb78025","timestamp":"2026-04-07T14:25:23.631Z","parentId":"9619058e-70a4-4b98-9fd2-e365804419aa"}
